ast1=Pounds|first1=Norman J. G.|isbn=9780521311090|url=https://archive.org/details/historicalgeogra00poun|url-access=registration}}\n* ''Rand McNally Atlas of World History'' (1983), maps #76-81. Published in Britain as the ''Hamlyn Historical Atlas'' [https://archive.org/details/randmcnallyatlas00 online free]\n* Robertson, Charles Grant. ''An historical atlas of modern Europe from 1789 to 1922 with an historical and explanatory text'' (1922) [https://archive.org/details/HistoricalAtlas online free]\n* Talbert, Richard J.A. ''Barrington Atlas of the Greek and Roman World for iPad'' (Princeton UP 2014) {{ISBN|978-1-4008-4876-8}}; 102 interactive color maps from archaic Greece to the Late Roman Empire.\n* [https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Historical_atlas ''Historical Atlas''] Wikipedia maps; no copyright\n* [https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Atlas_of_Germany ''Atlas of Germany''] Wikipedia maps; no copyright\n \n===Major nations===\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1007/978-1-349-24974-9|title=A History of the British Isles|year=1996|last1=Black|first1=Jeremy|isbn=978-1-349-24976-3}}\n* Carr, Raymond, ed. ''Spain: A history'' (2000)\n* Clark, Christopher M. ''Iron kingdom: the rise and downfall of Prussia, 1600-1947'' (2006)\n* Davies, Norman. ''The Isles: A History'' (2001), Britain and Ireland\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1017/CBO9781139019330|title=A Concise History of Italy|year=2013|last1=Duggan|first1=Christopher|isbn=9781139019330}}\n* Fraser, Rebecca. ''The Story of Britain: From the Romans to the Present: A Narrative History'' (2006)\n* Holborn, Hajo. vol 1: ''A History of Modern Germany: The Reformation''; vol 2: ''A History of Modern Germany: 1648-1840''; vol 3: ''A history of modern Germany: 1840-1945'' (1959). a standard scholarly survey.\n* Kamen, Henry. ''A concise history of Spain'' ( 1973)\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1017/CHOL9780521472999.002|chapter=Introduction|title=The Cambridge History of Scandinavia|pages=1\u201312|year=2003|last1=Helle|first1=Knut|isbn=9781139053570}}\n* Holmes, George, ed. ''The Oxford illustrated history of medieval Europe'' (2001).\n* Holmes, George, ed. ''The Oxford illustrated history of Italy'' (1997)\n* Jones, Colin. ''The Cambridge Illustrated History of France'' (1999)\n* Kitchen, Martin ''The Cambridge Illustrated History of Germany'' (1996).\n* [[Morgan, Kenneth O.]], ed. ''The Oxford illustrated history of Britain'' (1984)\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1017/CBO9781139084710|title=A Concise History of France|year=2013|last1=Price|first1=Roger|isbn=9781139084710}}\n* [[Nicholas V. Riasanovsky|Riasanovsky, Nicholas V.]], and Mark D. Steinberg. ''A History of Russia'' (2 vol. 2010)\n* Sagarra, Eda. ''A social history of Germany'' (2003)\n* Tombs, Robert, ''The English and their History'' (2014) advanced history; [https://www.theguardian.com/books/2014/nov/17/the-english-and-their-history-review-robert-tombs-resounding-importance online review]\n* {{cite book|doi=10.4159/9780674915909|title=Heart of Europe|year=2016|last1=Wilson|first1=Peter H.|isbn=9780674915909}}\n \n===Classical===\n* Boardman, John, et al. eds. ''The Oxford History of Greece and the Hellenistic World'' (2nd ed. 2002) 520 pp\n* Boardman, John, et al. eds. ''The Oxford History of the Roman World'' (2001)\n* Cartledge, Paul. ''The Cambridge Illustrated History of Ancient Greece'' (2002)\n \n===Late Roman===\n* [[Peter Heather|Heather, Peter]]. ''Empires and Barbarians: The Fall of Rome and the Birth of Europe'' (Oxford University Press; 2010); 734 pages; Examines the migrations, trade, and other phenomena that shaped a recognizable entity of Europe in the first millennium.\n* Jones, A.H.M. ''The Later Roman Empire, 284-602: A Social, Economic, and Administrative Survey'' (2 Vol. 1964)\n* Mitchell, Stephen. ''A History of the Later Roman Empire, AD 284-641: The Transformation of the Ancient World'' (2006)\n \n===Medieval===\n* Davis, R.H.C. ''A History of Medieval Europe'' (2nd ed. 2000)\n* Ferguson, Wallace K. ''Europe in Transition, 1300-1520'' (1962) [https://www.questia.com/library/1608627/europe-in-transition-1300-1520 online]\n* Hanawalt, Barbara. ''The Middle Ages: An Illustrated History'' (1999)\n* Holmes, George, ed. ''The Oxford Illustrated History of Medieval Europe'' (2001)\n* Koenigsberger, H.G. ''Medieval Europe 400-1500'' (1987)\n* Riddle, John M. ''A history of the Middle Ages, 300-1500'' (2008)\n \n===Early modern===\n* {{cite journal|doi=10.1093/acprof:oso/9780198227458.001.0001|title=The Culture of Power and the Power of Culture|year=2002|last1=Blanning|first1=T. C. W.|isbn=9780198227458}}\n* Cameron, Euan. ''Early Modern Europe: An Oxford History'' (2001)\n* Friedrich, Carl J. ''The Age of the Baroque, 1610-1660'' (1962); Despite the title, this is a wide-ranging Social, cultural, political and diplomatic history of Europe; [https://archive.org/details/ageofbaroque100frie 14-day borrowing copy]\n* Hesmyr, Atle. ''Scandinavia in the Early Modern Era; From Peasant Revolts and Witch Hunts to Constitution Drafting Yeomen'' (2014)\n* {{cite book|doi=10.4324/9781315837093|title=The Rise of the Great Powers 1648 - 1815|year=2014|last1=McKay|first1=Derek|isbn=9781315837093}}\n* Rice, Eugene F. ''The Foundations of Early Modern Europe, 1460-1559'' (2nd ed. 1994) 240 pp\n* Merriman, John. ''A History of Modern Europe: From the Renaissance to the Present'' (3rd ed. 2009, 2 vol), 1412 pp\n* [[Hamish Scott (historian)|Scott, Hamish]], ed. ''The Oxford Handbook of Early Modern European History, 1350-1750: Volume I: Peoples and Place'' (2015).\n** {{cite journal|doi=10.1093/oxfordhb/9780199597260.001.0001|title=The Oxford Handbook of Early Modern European History, 1350-1750|year=2015|isbn=9780199597260}}\n* Stoye, John. ''Europe Unfolding, 1648-1688'' (2nd ed. 2000).\n* {{cite book|doi=10.4324/9780203425985|title=The Making of Modern Europe, 1648-1780|year=2003|last1=Treasure|first1=Geoffrey|isbn=9780203425985}}\n* Wiesner, Merry E. ''Early Modern Europe, 1450-1789'' (Cambridge History of Europe) (2006)\n \n===Past perspectives on modern European history===\n* Earle, Edward Mead. [https://archive.org/details/outlineofmodernh00earl ''An Outline of Modern History; A Syllabus with Map Studies'']. New York: Macmillan Co, 1921.\n* Taylor, William Cooke, Charles Duke Yonge, and G.W. Cox. [https://books.google.com/books?id=bjQYAAAAYAAJ ''The Student's Manual of Modern History; Containing the Rise and Progress of the Principal European Nations, Their Political History, and the Changes in Their Social Condition; with a History of the Colonies Founded by Europeans'']. 1880.\n \n===19th century===\n* Anderson, M.S. ''The Ascendancy of Europe: 1815-1914'' (3rd ed. 2003)\n* Blanning, T.C.W. ed. ''The Nineteenth Century: Europe 1789-1914'' (Short Oxford History of Europe) (2000) 320 pp\n* Brinton, Crane. ''A Decade of Revolution, 1789-1799'' (1934).\" [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.74354 online] in Langer series on history of Europe.\n* Bruun, Geoffrey. ''Europe and the French Imperium, 1799-1814'' (1938) [https://archive.org/download/in.ernet.dli.2015.183653/2015.183653.Europe-And-The-French-Imperium-1799-1814_text.pdf online].\n* Cameron, Rondo. ''France and the Economic Development of Europe, 1800-1914: Conquests of Peace and Seeds of War'' (1961), wide-ranging economic and business history.\n* Evans, Richard J. ''The Pursuit of Power: Europe 1815-1914'' (2016), 934 pp\n* Gildea, Robert. ''Barricades and Borders: Europe 1800-1914'' (Short Oxford History of the Modern World) (3rd ed. 2003) 544 pp, [https://www.questia.com/read/55547824/barricades-and-borders-europe-1800-1914 online 2nd ed, 1996]\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1007/978-1-4039-3757-5|title=Napoleon and the Transformation of Europe|year=2003|last1=Grab|first1=Alexander|isbn=978-0-333-68275-3}}\n* Kertesz, G.A. ed ''Documents in the Political History of the European Continent 1815-1939'' (1968), 507 pp; several hundred short documents\n* Mason, David S. ''A Concise History of Modern Europe: Liberty, 